revision.text:
'''A'ra''' is a tutelary god worshipped in [[pre-Islamic Arabia]], particularly northern Arabia.
{{Pre-Islamic Arabian deities}}

==Sacrifices==
The name implies a holy place or an altar, but its Arabic root also means "to dye". It is implied that many sacrifices (which may include children) were offered to the idol, staining it with blood.<ref>Michael Jordan (2004, 1993), ''Dictionary of Gods and Goddesses, Second Edition''</ref>

