{{coord| 21|18|39|N| 157|51|43|W| type:landmark_region:US-HI| display=title}}
The '''Arts District''' is a neighborhood in [[Honolulu]] located west of [[downtown Honolulu]]'s [[Hawaii Capital Historic District]] and on the eastern edge of [[Chinatown, Honolulu|Chinatown]].  It spans just over 12 blocks, bounded by Bethel and Smith Streets and Nimitz Highway and Beretania Street.<ref>{{cite web |title= The Arts District Honolulu |url= http://www.artsdistricthonolulu.com |work= web site |accessdate= 2010-04-08}}</ref>

It is home to cultural institutions, performing arts venues (including the historic [[Hawaii Theatre]]), galleries, and arts events. The [[Merchant Street Historic District]] is just to the south.

