{{Political corruption sidebar|image=[[File:Flag of the United States.svg|150 px]]}} '''Corruption in the United States''' is the act of a local, state or federal official using some form of influence or being influenced in some way, typically through [[bribery]]. Corruption is used to the advantage of the government official and a person or group of people.
The [[United States|U.S.]] is the 18th least [[corrupt]] country in the world, according to the 2016 [[Corruption Perceptions Index]] by [[Transparency International]].<ref>{{Cite web | title = Corruption Perceptions Index 2016 | publisher = Transparency International | date = January 25, 2017 | accessdate = April 10, 2017 | url = http://www.transparency.org/news/feature/corruption_perceptions_index_2016 }}</ref>
