{{Infobox Journal | title = Theoretical Linguistics | cover = [[File:Theoretical Linguistics (journal).gif]] | editor = [[Manfred Krifka]] | discipline = [[Theoretical linguistics]] | abbreviation = Theor. Linguist. | publisher = [[Mouton de Gruyter]] | country = [[Germany]] | frequency = Three times a year | history = 1975–present | openaccess = | impact = 0.824 | impact-year = 2012 | website = http://www.degruyter.com/rs/384_411_ENU_h.htm | link1 = http://www.atypon-link.com/WDG/loi/thli | link1-name = Atypon Link | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | ISSN = 0301-4428 | eISSN = 1613-4060 }}
'''''Theoretical Linguistics''''' is an international [[peer-review]]ed journal of [[theoretical linguistics]] published by [[Mouton de Gruyter]]. Since 2001 Prof. [[Manfred Krifka]] ([[Humboldt University of Berlin]]) has been its editor. Each issue contains one long target article, together with several shorter reactions, comments and reflections on it. The issues from 2004 on are accessible online with subscription via [[Atypon Link]].
[[Category:Linguistics journals]] [[Category:Publications established in 1975]] [[Category:English-language journals]] [[Category:Triannual journals]] [[Category:Walter de Gruyter academic journals]]

'''''Too Much To Know: Managing Scholarly Information before the Modern Age''''' ([[Yale University Press]], 2010) is a bestselling book by the American intellectual historian [[Ann M. Blair]]. The book deals with the concept of [[information overload]]. Blair argues that the feeling of being overwhelmed by information is not unique to the [[digital age]]. Instead it has existed since antiquity and in many cultures.
==Reception==
''[[The New Yorker]]'' named the book as one of the best books of 2011.<ref>[http://www.newyorker.com/arts/reviews/brieflynoted/2011/12/19/111219crbn_brieflynoted?currentPage=all newyorker.com]</ref> It was also praised by the ''[[Washington Post]]'',<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/01/12/AR2011011207505.html washingtonpost.com]</ref> Rorotoko,<ref>[http://rorotoko.com/interview/20110706_blair_ann_too_much_to_know_managing_information_before_modern_age/ rorotoko.com]</ref> and ''[[Times Higher Education]]''.<ref>[http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/story.asp?storycode=415024 timeshighereducation.com]</ref>
