{{Infobox journal | title = University of Denver Water Law Review | cover = | former_name = <!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation=Univ. Denver Water Law Rev. | bluebook = U. Denv. Water L. Rev. | discipline = [[Water law]] | editor = Sarah Rice | publisher = [[Sturm College of Law]], [[University of Denver]] | country = United States | history = 1997-present | frequency = Biannually | ISSN = 1521-3455 | OCLC = 39000677 | website = http://duwaterlawreview.com/ | link1 = http://duwaterlawreview.com/category/posts/ | link1-name = Blog | link2 = http://duwaterlawreview.com/archive/ | link2-name = Online archives }}
The '''University of Denver Water Law Review''' is a [[law review|law journal]] focused on ideas, information, and legal and policy analyses concerning water law. Launched in 1997, it is published by students at the [[Sturm College of Law]] at the [[University of Denver]] in Colorado. <ref>http://duwaterlawreview.com/about/</ref>
== Overview == The ''Water Law Review'' publishes two issues each year and contains articles, case notes, book reviews, case summaries and legislative updates written by lawyers, academics, and students. The review also provides an online supplement discussing the legal and policy implications of current events. <ref>http://duwaterlawreview.com/category/posts/</ref> Additionally, the review hosts an annual "Water Law Symposium" in the spring. <ref>http://duwaterlawreview.com/events/</ref>
